And there’s another layer here that matters:

You didn’t need ownership to feel validation.

That’s psychologically stable.

The dangerous version of this mindset is:

“They validated me.”

The stable version is:

“The pattern proved viable.”

That difference keeps you creative instead of defensive.

⸻

